<p>The docs for <a href="http://tornado.readthedocs.org/en/latest/_modules/tornado/tcpserver.html#TCPServer.stop" rel="nofollow"><code>tornado.tcpserver.TCPServer.stop</code></a> say:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Requests currently in progress may still continue after the server is stopped</p> </blockquote>  <p>However, to test for robustness I want to simulate a full crash of the server.</p>  <p>Is there a preferred way to abruptly terminate a tornado.TCPServer?  In particular I want to terminate all open sockets <em>ungracefully</em>.</p>